# btca - Better Context Agent

Use btca when the user asks about a specific library/framework, needs current API behavior, or explicitly says to use btca.

## Behavior
- Prefer `btca ask`; avoid the TUI.
- If unsure what's configured, run `btca config resources list`.
- If the user wants to add/change resources or models but omits details, ask for the missing info first.

## Core Commands
- Ask: `btca ask -r <resource> -q "<question>"`
- List: `btca config resources list`
- Add (git): `btca config resources add -n <name> -t git -u <url> -b <branch>`
- Add (local): `btca config resources add -n <name> -t local --path <absolutePath>`
- Remove: `btca config resources remove -n <name>`
- Change model: `btca config model -p <provider> -m <model>`
- Clear cache: `btca clear`

## Config Locations
- `~/.config/btca/btca.config.jsonc`
- `./btca.config.jsonc` (overrides global by name)
